comments: Smart (BOS) cleanly intercepts the pass from Poeltl (SAS) in the lane.
During the steal, Murray (SAS) and Williams III (BOS) engage and disengage, and the contact is marginal as it does not affect Williams III's ability to get to the pass.

Replay review of the foul called on Brown (BOS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. White (SAS) establishes himself in a legal guarding position in Brown's (BOS) path and absorbs the contact initiated by Brown on his driving shot attempt.

Brown (BOS) is established in his legally obtained position within White's (SAS) path and absorbs the marginal contact initiated by White during his cut. Brown keeps his hands and arms out to his side and does not use them to impede White's FOM.
Schroder (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position on Murray (SAS) during the drive. Also, Brown (BOS) avoids any contact with Murray's arm during his steal attempt.
Brown (BOS) legally contests Murray's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
Williams III (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Bates-Diop's (SAS) path and absorbs the contact on the pick.
White (SAS) makes clean ball contact to dislodge it from Brown (BOS) at the end of his drive. Any follow-through contact to Brown's arm after the dislodge is deemed incidental.
White (SAS) cleanly dislodges the ball from Brown (BOS) before he is in the lane for more than three seconds.
Vassell (SAS) makes contact to Smart's (BOS) arm at the end of the drive, which affects his ability to cleanly gather and pass the ball.
Vassell (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Schroder (BOS).
Williams III (BOS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
There is no clear and conclusive camera angle to overturn the call on the court of Murray (SAS) stepping on the sideline out of bounds before releasing his pass.
Williams III (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Murray's (SAS) path and absorbs the contact on the pick.
Poeltl (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Smart (BOS).

Brown (BOS) makes clean ball contact to dislodge it from White (SAS) in the backcourt. As he dislodges the ball, Brown's hand slides off of White's back and marginal contact occurs as his hand briefly gets caught in his jersey.
White (SAS) and Brown (BOS) dive to the ground in pursuit of the loose ball and White makes clean ball contact to tie it up. A jump ball is correctly called.

The ball is rebounded by Murray (SAS) with 23.5 seconds left on the game clock. Brown (BOS) then takes possession of the ball after dislodging it from White (SAS) with 15.7 seconds left. Therefore, an eight-second violation is not warranted and a jump ball after the clean tie-up is correctly called.
Murray (SAS) does not step on the sideline out of bounds before elevating and releasing his pass back inbounds.
Williams III (BOS) commits a take foul on Vassell (SAS).
During the inbound, Brown (BOS) and Murray (SAS) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs before the errant inbounds pass.
During the inbound, Smart (BOS) and Bates-Diop (SAS) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Landale's (SAS) arm grazes the rim while the shot is in the air, and the contact does not vibrate the basket or rim.
Murray (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt by Brown (BOS).
Smart (BOS) cleanly dislodges the ball from Bates-Diop (SAS) during the rebound. The game clock expires before the last-second shot attempt by Smart or any possible contact by Bates-Diop.
